name: Clean Energy Technologies
short_description: Clean Energy Technologies, Inc. designs, produces, and markets clean energy products and integrated solutions focused on energy efficiency.
long_description: Clean Energy Technologies, Inc. designs, produces, and markets clean energy products and integrated solutions focused on energy efficiency. The companyâ€™s principal product is the Clean Cycle, a generator that captures waste heat from various sources and turns it into electricity. It also offers a range of electrical, mechanical, and software engineering services; electronics manufacturing services; and supply chain management services. The company was formerly known as Probe Manufacturing, Inc. and changed its name to Clean Energy Technologies, Inc. in November 2015. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Costa Mesa, California. Clean Energy Technologies, Inc. is a subsidiary of MGW Investments I Limited.
